annotation.TEXT: Whoops! Well, I meant to catch the shell while letting the koopa drop, but that was kind of cool anyway.
Hmm... I'm thinking the theme of this level involves lots of note blocks.
D'oh! That's okay. I've got a replacement flower right here.
There's my "zwee".
Yeah, don't think that I didn't see that Yoshi coin up there a moment ago.
And there's me losing my cape like an idiot.
Well, that sucked. I was trying to see if I could clobber the Swooper with the ? block, and I got clobbered instead.
Why am I bothering to collect this flower? There's no points or reserve items in this hack.
This unlocks the upper-left pipe, which I kind of expected. Okay, now I've only been playing for about four and a half minutes here, so let's go through the pipe and play the next level!
Ah, it's this music again. Now, normally, I wouldn't bother with the label in the upper-left corner for reused music, but I will this time, in case you guys forgot.
My toe! My toe! Fortunately, I just revealed a cape feather, which will patch me right up!
Oh, come on. That Goomba missed both of them? What happened to my awesome Goomba accuracy?
BAKABAKABAKABAKABAKA!
BGM: Sonic Triple Trouble - Meta Junglira Zone
BGM: CUSTOM - Seventh Sound by ThinkOneMoreTime
Uh, oh. A red level. Well, I was going to end the video here, but now I have to scope out whether or not both of the exits from this level lead to playable levels...
I wonder if I could get a 1-up stomping combo around here...
I think I went a little underboard (Is that even a word?) with that slide...
Now, will the game troll me again with an incomplete level?
Whoa, the plant life certainly seems to have taken over this place.
Yep, that worked, though I don't know if it was worth the trouble.
BGM: CUSTOM - Star Shock by ThinkOneMoreTime
Zwee!
...And it's two-way.
Yeah, I got my 1-up stomping combo!
Nice accuracy with that Goomba kick!
I'm going to guess that this level's theme revolves around slopes and sliding koopas.
Yep. I totally got a totally useless mushroom. Totally.
Alright, so we've got more moons and stars etched into the dirt, and some platforming to do here...
That's every Yoshi coin here. Now, as for the goal, I want to try something if I can...
BGM: Project Justice (Rival Schools 2) - Taiyo School Rooftop
Ooh, that last Yoshi looks a bit tricky, but I can get it!
Welcome back to Lunar Legends! Last time, I had just defeated the fake dragonmaster on Lann Island, and was heading back to Vane to make my report... Wait, that's a different game.
So, what awaits us in the rest of world 3? Find out next time, on quite possibly the finale of Lunar Legends!
What are these, fuzzy hotlines?
Double kill!
Ooh, and now I've found a pipe that goes somewhere...
Oh, and now we've got coins etched into the dirt.
Let me guess... Boss under construction?
Up next is Kiwi Castle. Alright, let's-a-go!
So, by carefully touching the goal square from the right (or maybe below), I can actually claim the item. (Of course, it's still going to be useless most of the time.)
Yeah, that's a tricky multi-coin block to empty out.

I was kind of hoping that I could somehow cape thwack that Lava Lotus while bouncing on it. (Like how sometimes, when you try to spin jump on something while caped, and you end up cape thwacking it instead.)
Now, I had just opened up Wiki Woods 3, so let's enter it and look at all of the user-created content, and maybe add or edit stuff as needed... Wait, that doesn't sound right...
Well, right away, you know this level's gotta be good, with this awesome-sounding music playing!
Oh, I should've tried making a block factory here...
Watch out! The circles are starting to go elliptical!
That's the last Yoshi coin.
And now the food naming theme continues with Caramel Hills.
I guess I'm stuck with fireballs for now.
Okay, that one coin is totally not worth risking my life for.
Yep.
Also, this cape is awesome. Let's see if I can maintain it for a while this time...
There's a few Rexes, but by themselves, only allow me six stomps...
And so has the buzz saw life, it seems. Oh, and I think I'll be keeping my cape, by the way.
And there's our secret exit.
I see that Swooper up there, and it could interfere with my next jump. Is there a way I can bait it to drop down early?
I feel like I should've taken a hit where I made my fifth stomp there, but whatever. The game's stomping hit detection is weird with some enemies.
Hey there fuzzy. How's it going?
I think I went a little overboard with that slide...
Okay, there's the pipe that had the secret exit, and there's the goal just past it, so this level is done.
Well, that's two of the three worlds of this demo down, and I still haven't collected a moon yet! There'd better be a collectable moon in world 3!
To be continued...
I wonder if I could maintain a stomping combo through this entire level if I were TAS-ing...
There sure are a lot of stars and moons in the dirt...

Ha! Yep, I'm thinking that if I'm carrying something when I hit the goal, it always transforms into an item like usual. However, if I overlap the goal square for more than one frame, the item that just appeared will vanish on the goal retriggers.
Yep, so no Brown Switch Palace for us. Now, I could've ended the video here, but I may as well just quickly get the normal exit from Caramel Hills 2...
This music sounds pretty cool. I wonder what it is...
